  "body": "- [ ] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nTruffle no longer appears to work correctly with RPC providers that do not implement `evm_snapshot`\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n```\r\nnpm init -y\r\nnpm i truffle ganache-cli\r\nsed -i 's/snapshot/disablesnapshot/g' ./node_modules/ganache-cli/build/ganache-core.node.cli.js\r\nnpx truffle unbox metacoin \r\n```\r\nThe `sed` here disables the `evm_snapshot` endpoint for the instance of `ganache-cli` we're installing. You will need to say yes to the prompt from the `unbox` command.\r\n```\r\nsed -i '8,33{s|//||g}' truffle-config.js\r\nsed -i 's/7545/8545/g' truffle-config.js\r\ncp ./test/metacoin.js ./test/metacoin2.js\r\n``` \r\nThis sets up the config file correctly to connect to `ganache-cli`, and adds extra test blocks required to trigger the error.\r\nIn separate windows:\r\n```\r\nnpx ganache-cli\r\nnpx truffle test\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nThe tests run correctly.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nThe tests fail with the output\r\n\r\n```\r\n  1) Contract: MetaCoin\r\n       \"before all\" hook: prepare suite for \"should put 10000 MetaCoin in the first account\":\r\n     ReferenceError: config is not defined\r\n      at TestRunner.initialize (node_modules/truffle/build/webpack:/packages/core/lib/testing/TestRunner.js:44:1)\r\n      at Context.<anonymous> (node_modules/truffle/build/webpack:/packages/core/lib/testing/Test.js:315:1)\r\n      at processImmediate (internal/timers.js:456:21)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Ubuntu 20.04\r\n* Ethereum client: ganache-cli / parity\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): `Truffle v5.1.48 (core: 5.1.48)`\r\n* node version (`node --version`): `Node v12.16.3`\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`):  `6.14.4`\r\n\r\n## Additional investigation\r\n \r\nI think this is because there is a global `config` floating around that [this](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/develop/packages/core/lib/testing/TestRunner.js#L44) line manages to use, that gets clobbered during the redeployment. The second redeployment required then fails.\r\n\r\nThis is supported by the fact that if you monkeypatch `truffle` thusly, the tests pass:\r\n```\r\nsed -i 's/this.config.resolver = new Resolver(config, true);/this.config.resolver = new Resolver(this.config, true);/g' ./node_modules/truffle/build/commands.bundled.js\r\n```\r\n\r\nThough there may be unintended consequences to this I haven't seen.",
